        "### 7. RAG Chatbot Core Logic\n",
        "\n",
        "This section defines the core functions for our RAG chatbot:\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **`retrieve_chunks(query, k)`**: Takes a user query, generates its embedding, and searches the FAISS index to find the `k` most relevant document chunks.\n",
        "*   **`format_prompt(query, retrieved_chunks)`**: Constructs a prompt for the LLM by combining the user's query with the retrieved context from the documents.\n",
        "*   **`generate_response(prompt)`**: Feeds the formatted prompt into the local LLM to get a generated answer.\n",
        "\n",
        "*Note: `distilgpt2` is a basic language model and its responses might sometimes be generic or not fully coherent. For better quality, a larger local model would be needed, which might exceed Colab's free tier resources.*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "b3d9c81b",
        "outputId": "cff395c2-6c21-486f-f2ea-afabc0596d40"
      },
      "source": [
        "def retrieve_chunks(query, k=3):\n",
        "    if not all_document_chunks:\n",
        "        return []\n",
        "    query_embedding = embedding_model.encode([query])\n",
        "    distances, indices = faiss_index.search(np.array(query_embedding).astype('float32'), k)\n",
        "    retrieved_content = [all_document_chunks[idx] for idx in indices[0]]\n",
        "    return retrieved_content\n",
        "\n",
        "def format_prompt(query, retrieved_chunks):\n",
        "    context = \"\\n\".join(retrieved_chunks)\n",
        "    prompt = f\"Context: {context}\\n\\nQuestion: {query}\\n\\nAnswer:\"\n",
        "    return prompt\n",
        "\n",
        "def generate_response(prompt, max_new_tokens=100):\n",
        "    # max_new_tokens is set to limit the length of distilgpt2's output\n",
        "    response = llm_pipeline(prompt, max_new_tokens=max_new_tokens, num_return_sequences=1,\n",
        "                            pad_token_id=llm_pipeline.tokenizer.eos_token_id)[0]['generated_text']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # The LLM will re-state the prompt, so we need to extract only the answer part\n",
        "    # This is a heuristic and might need adjustment depending on the LLM's output style\n",
        "    answer_prefix = \"Answer:\"\n",
        "    if answer_prefix in response:\n",
        "        answer_start_index = response.rfind(answer_prefix) # Use rfind for robustness\n",
        "        extracted_answer = response[answer_start_index + len(answer_prefix):].strip()\n",
        "        # Further clean up by removing subsequent questions or incomplete sentences\n",
        "        if \"Question:\" in extracted_answer:\n",
        "            extracted_answer = extracted_answer.split(\"Question:\")[0].strip()\n",
        "        return extracted_answer\n",
        "    return response.strip() # Fallback if 'Answer:' isn't found\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"RAG core functions defined.\")"
      ],
